<title>VENEZUELA: Venezuela rules out dollar-based bank accounts.</title>
<headline>Venezuela rules out dollar-based bank accounts.</headline>
<dateline>CARACAS 1997-08-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Venezuela will not allow banks to offer accounts in foreign currencies, despite requests by some institutions to do so, the central bank's president, Antonio Casas Gonzalez, said Tuesday.</p>
<p>&quot;It would not be convenient because it would dollarize the economy,&quot; Casas told reporters at a ceremony to inaugurate the World Bank's new offices in Caracas.</p>
<p>Casas acknowledged that some commercial banks had asked for permission to offer such accounts, but he said the central bank's top priority was re-establishing confidence in the local bolivar currency.</p>
<p>((-- Omar Lugo, Caracas newsroom, 582 505 2600))</p>
